      "writtenOn": "2019-03-04T20:58:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e It is intended that SkCodec will initialize all pixels\n\nAh, there might be a second misunderstanding... I\u0027m focusing on the initialization obligations between SkCodec (including its SkWuffsCodec subclass) and the GIF library (i.e. Wuffs). I think you\u0027re focusing on between SkCodec\u0027s caller and SkCodec...\n\nStill, to clarify, suppose frame #0 has a frame rect that is smaller than the image rect. The pixels outside the frame rect still need to be zero-initialized, right? Who should do the initializing: the GIF library, SkCodec or the SkCodec\u0027s caller? Is this frame #0 still considered independent?",
