      "message": "\u003e I do not understand what a \"super-independent\" frame is\n\nSo, the zero-init is currently done by SkWuffsCodec. \"Super-independent\" would mean that that zero-initting could be skipped, as Wuffs will overwrite the whole buffer. For example, (frame_rect \u003d\u003d image_rect) and opaque and fully received and no decoding errors. That\u0027s what I meant by the \"super-independent\" concept, although that last clause makes it a non-trivial concept to implement, in practice.\n\n\n\u003e Yep! Thanks for catching :)\n\nOK, I\u0027ll think about how to re-word the proposed comments to make that distinction clearer. I\u0027ll ping the review when it\u0027s ready.",
