      "writtenOn": "2019-03-04T20:33:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Looking at this some more, I almost thought this might not be redundant. Although it\u0027s a similar check, it could be checking a different frame. Let\u0027s say we have the following frames:\n\n0: restore bg, fills the canvas\n1: restore bg, smaller than the canvas\n2: \u003cany disposal method\u003e, larger than frame 1\n\nWe\u0027re checking to see whether 2 is independent. It doesn\u0027t hit IND4 condition, because that is checking frame 1. But then we update prevFrame to be 1\u0027s required frame. We still couldn\u0027t hit IND7. 0 won\u0027t be 1\u0027s required frame, unless it is not restore bg, or it doesn\u0027t fill the canvas.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 765,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 766,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "1d001032647bb2f658edc8a71fd28aaacd5e9fe6",
